---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Attis Campaigns — Explicit Studio">

  <article class="project-page reveal">

    <div class="project-page__hero-image placeholder">
      Attis Campaigns — Hero Image
    </div>

    <h1 class="project-page__title">Attis Campaigns</h1>
    <p class="project-page__subtitle">Two viral campaigns that exposed nerves. Zero ad spend. Massive reach.</p>

    <div class="project-details">
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Client</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">Attis</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Industry</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">Biohacking / Wellness</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Services</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">Strategy, Campaign, Product Design</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Year</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">2024</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Result</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">850+ orders &middot; 250k+ views</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-page__label">The landscape</p>
    <p class="project-page__body">After building the community, Attis needed to convert attention into revenue. But typical health-brand advertising — clean product shots, benefit-focused copy, influencer unboxings — would have killed the edge that made the brand interesting.</p>

    <div class="project-page__full-image placeholder">
      Attis Campaigns — Image
    </div>

    <p class="project-page__label">The insight</p>
    <p class="project-page__body">We ran two campaigns designed to expose nerves. Each one made people uncomfortable enough to stop scrolling, curious enough to click, and convinced enough to buy. The campaigns leaned into Attis's counter-cultural positioning rather than softening it for conversion.</p>

    <div class="project-page__full-image placeholder">
      Attis Campaigns — Image
    </div>
    <div class="project-page__image-grid">
      <div class="placeholder">Attis Campaigns — Image</div>
      <div class="placeholder">Attis Campaigns — Image</div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-page__label">The outcome</p>
    <p class="project-page__body">Two viral campaigns. 850+ product orders. 250k+ organic views. The brand maintained its edge while proving that provocative creative isn't just for awareness — it converts.</p>

    <div class="project-page__next">
      <a href="/work/origin-one">
        Next project &mdash; Origin One <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach((el) => {
    observer.observe(el);
  });
</script>
